In a speech delivered in the East Room, President Joe Biden expressed his gratitude to teachers and highlighted the importance of their role in shaping the lives of students. He praised his wife, Jill Biden, who is a teacher herself, and emphasized the impact that teachers had on his own life, particularly during his struggle with stuttering. President Biden acknowledged the challenges that teachers faced during the pandemic, including having to adapt to remote learning and provide support to students and their families. He commended their dedication and resilience and emphasized the need to invest in education, including increased funding for schools, teacher diversity, and special education. President Biden also called for high-speed internet access for all students and expressed his commitment to supporting teachers and ensuring they receive the recognition and compensation they deserve.